          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The M422 Mighty Mite lives in the shadow of its military brethren. Here's why this overlooked hero deserves your attention",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h3",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Military vehicles are responsible for pioneering all manner of technical origination. Through wartime innovation, engineering marvels designed to support allied forces usually find homes in home-bred production vehicles.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Willys Jeep, British Land Rover and Toyota Land Cruiser all claim credit for pushing the boundaries of mechanical dependability during times of conflict, but there is one forgotten vehicle that deserves attention. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "linebreak",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "linebreak",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 3,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "More American Greats",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "type": "linebreak",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
